{
  "texts": [
    "As shown in Fig. 26, the overall framework is divided into three parts: (a) Step 1 is called the proposal network.",
    "The proposal generation network is used to calculate the probability of action in all video clips; (b) Step 2 is called the classification network.",
    "Classification networks are used to classify different actions and backgrounds; (c) Step 3 is called the localization network.",
    "The similar output of the location and classification networks is still the probability of each action.",
    "In training, overlap loss based on the IOU score is increased to make better use of the overlap rate."
  ]
}